<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[Crêpes: sieve flour into milk, trying to avoid lumps. Add the beaten eggs, pinch of salt, and melted butter. Mix and stand 2 hours]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Rub butter on flat pans, and cook crêpes in it. Lay over a table, next to each other]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Filling: Chop onion and rosemary and sauté in a butter and oil mixture, 5 mins. Add diced pumpkin and cook diluting with water 20-30mins.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Béchamelle: Melt the butter in another pot, remove from fire and sieve the flour in. Put back on fire and cook while mixing until browned.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Slowly add the milk, while still mixing. When done, season with salt, pepper, and nutmeg. Set aside.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[When the pumpkin is tender, mash it with a food processor and add to béchamelle]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Spoon sauce over each crêpe, drop bits of walnuts and cheese cubes over sauce, and roll up.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Lay in a buttered baking tray, pour melted butter and grated parmesan over it, and bake 10 mins at 180°]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
